 :tx/rationale "ATT-2 DEEP SPEC: COMPOSITE ATTENTION FORMULA (FINAL). For a context block with label L, active task T, and recommended action A: attention(L, T, A) = surprisal(L) × relevance(L, T) × actionability(L, A) × boost(L). WHERE: surprisal(L) = 1/sqrt(max(1, count(L))) if content unchanged, else 1.0 (content-change reset, INV-ATTENTION-007). relevance(L, T) = jaccard(spec_refs(L), traces_to(T)) if T exists, else 0.5. Range [0.3, 1.0] with 0.3 floor (every block has minimum relevance). actionability(L, A) = 1.0 if L contains A.command substring, 0.7 if L mentions A.entity, 0.5 if namespace_overlap(L, A.spec_refs), 0.2 otherwise. boost(L) = (1 + hebbian_boost(L)) × learned_weight(L). hebbian_boost decays 0.5x per session, learned_weight is persistent. Default boost = (1+0) × 1.0 = 1.0. PROPERTIES: (1) attention in (0, infinity) but practically in [0.01, 3.0]. (2) Monotone in each factor (increasing any factor increases attention). (3) Multiplicative composition ensures ALL factors matter — a block with zero relevance has near-zero attention regardless of surprisal. (4) The boost factor is the ONLY learned component initially. Everything else is computed from observables."
